# Day 31 – Sets in Python

## What is a Set?

A Set is an unordered collection of unique elements.

### Example

```python
numbers = {1, 2, 3, 4, 5}

print(numbers)
```

Output

```text
{1, 2, 3, 4, 5}
```

---

# Basic Set Operations

## Add Element

```python
numbers = {1, 2, 3}

numbers.add(4)

print(numbers)
```

Output

```text
{1, 2, 3, 4}
```

---

## Remove Element

```python
numbers = {1, 2, 3}

numbers.remove(2)

print(numbers)
```

Output

```text
{1, 3}
```

---

## Check Element Exists

```python
numbers = {1, 2, 3}

print(2 in numbers)
```

Output

```text
True
```

